definitions.definition: Arriving upon or on top of (speaking of a physical or metaphorical movement).
examples: My cat just jumped onto the keyboard.
A new drug has just come onto the market .
The thought-police were onto my plans of world domination.

definitions.definition: Being an onto function with a codomain of (see below).
examples: The exponential function maps the set of real numbers onto the set of positive real numbers.

main_definition: Arriving upon or on top of (speaking of a physical or metaphorical movement).
